/-- **The Hecke continuation package for the Dedekind zeta function**
(interface designed 2026-07-23 as the sound cut of the deep
explicit-formula leaf `dedekind_explicit_formula_fejer`): the entire
completed zeta `őĺ_K(s) = s(s‚ąí1)¬∑Z_K(s)`, where
`Z_K(s) = |d_K|^{s/2}¬∑őď_‚ĄĚ(s)^{r‚āĀ}¬∑őď_‚Ąā(s)^{r‚āā}¬∑ő∂_K(s)` is the completed
Dedekind zeta function (J. Neukirch, *Algebraic Number Theory*,
VII (5.10), with `őď_‚ĄĚ(s) = ŌÄ^{-s/2}őď(s/2)` and
`őď_‚Ąā(s) = 2¬∑(2ŌÄ)^{-s}őď(s)` from VII ¬ß4), together with EXACTLY the
analytic facts consumed by the contour argument of Poitou's
Propositions 1‚Äď3 (G. Poitou, *Sur les petits discriminants*,
S√©m. Delange‚ÄďPisot‚ÄďPoitou 18 (1976/77), exp. 6, pp. 6-01‚Äď6-06).
Field-by-field truth and role:

* `xi`, `differentiable`: `Z_K` is meromorphic with only simple poles
  at `0` and `1` (Hecke; Neukirch VII (5.10)), so `s(s‚ąí1)Z_K(s)` is
  ENTIRE ‚ÄĒ carrying `őĺ` rather than the meromorphic `Z_K` makes every
  field a statement about a total function.
* `eq_of_one_lt_re`: the defining formula on the half-plane of
  absolute convergence, tying `őĺ` to the pin's raw Dirichlet series
  `NumberField.dedekindZeta`.  By the identity theorem this field
  determines `xi` uniquely, so all other fields ‚ÄĒ and any per-instance
  theorem stated about a `pkg` below ‚ÄĒ are facts about THE completed
  zeta, not about an arbitrary choice: the cut cannot smuggle in a
  degenerate instance.
* `funcEq`: Hecke's functional equation `Z_K(s) = Z_K(1‚ąís)` (Neukirch
  VII (5.10)) in `őĺ`-form; `(1‚ąís)((1‚ąís)‚ąí1) = s(s‚ąí1)` makes the two
  normalizations agree.
* `conj_symm`: Schwarz reflection `őĺ(sŐĄ) = conj (őĺ(s))` ‚ÄĒ true on
  `re s > 1` since every factor of `eq_of_one_lt_re` has real
  coefficients, hence everywhere by the identity theorem.  Pairs the
  zeros `ŌĀ` and `ŌĀŐĄ` with equal multiplicities in the symmetric
  truncations of the zero sum.
* `ne_zero_of_one_lt_re`: Euler-product nonvanishing (Neukirch
  VII (5.2)) times nonvanishing of `őď`, of `s(s‚ąí1)`, and of powers of
  positive reals.  (Nonvanishing on the closed boundary line
  `re s = 1` ‚ÄĒ de la Vall√©e Poussin for `ő∂_K`, plus the nonzero
  class-number-formula residue at `s = 1` itself ‚ÄĒ is deliberately NOT
  a field: it is derivable from this interface together with the
  pin's `NumberField.tendsto_sub_one_mul_dedekindZeta_nhdsGT`, and
  belongs inside the eventual proof of the zero-sum leaf
  `DedekindContinuation.fejer_zero_sum_tendsto`.)
* `growth`: the order-one bound `‚ÄĖőĺ(s)‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ exp(C¬∑‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ¬∑log ‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ)` off the
  disc `‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ < 2` (S. Lang, *Algebraic Number Theory*, XIII ¬ß5): by
  Stirling on the archimedean factors and the trivial bound
  `|ő∂_K(s)| ‚Č§ ő∂(re s)^n` on `re s ‚Č• 2`, extended by `funcEq` and
  Phragm√©n‚ÄďLindel√∂f to the intermediate strip.  This single true
  growth field is what the Jensen-formula zero counting
  `N(T+1) ‚ąí N(T) = O(log T)` and Landau's horizontal estimates
  (Poitou p. 6-02, citing E. Landau, *Algebraische Zahlen*, p. 122)
  will be built from ‚ÄĒ mathlib has no Hadamard factorization, so the
  zero-sum leaf must manufacture those counts from this bound. -/
structure DedekindContinuation (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K] where
  /-- The entire completed Dedekind zeta `őĺ_K(s) = s(s‚ąí1)¬∑Z_K(s)`. -/
  xi : ‚Ąā ‚Üí ‚Ąā
  /-- `őĺ_K` is entire (Hecke's theorem, Neukirch VII (5.10)). -/
  differentiable : Differentiable ‚Ąā xi
  /-- On `re s > 1` the completed zeta is
  `s(s‚ąí1)¬∑|d_K|^{s/2}¬∑őď_‚ĄĚ(s)^{r‚āĀ}¬∑őď_‚Ąā(s)^{r‚āā}¬∑ő∂_K(s)`. -/
  eq_of_one_lt_re : ‚ąÄ s : ‚Ąā, 1 < s.re ‚Üí
    xi s = s * (s - 1) * Complex.ofReal |(NumberField.discr K : ‚ĄĚ)| ^ (s / 2) *
      ((Real.pi : ‚Ąā) ^ (-s / 2) * Complex.Gamma (s / 2)) ^
        NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrRealPlaces K *
      ((2 : ‚Ąā) * ((2 * Real.pi : ‚ĄĚ) : ‚Ąā) ^ (-s) * Complex.Gamma s) ^
        NumberField.InfinitePlace.nrComplexPlaces K *
      NumberField.dedekindZeta K s
  /-- The functional equation `őĺ_K(1 ‚ąí s) = őĺ_K(s)`. -/
  funcEq : ‚ąÄ s : ‚Ąā, xi (1 - s) = xi s
  /-- Schwarz reflection: the Dirichlet coefficients are real. -/
  conj_symm : ‚ąÄ s : ‚Ąā, xi ((starRingEnd ‚Ąā) s) = (starRingEnd ‚Ąā) (xi s)
  /-- Euler-product nonvanishing on the open half-plane `re s > 1`. -/
  ne_zero_of_one_lt_re : ‚ąÄ s : ‚Ąā, 1 < s.re ‚Üí xi s ‚Č† 0
  /-- `őĺ_K` has order one: `‚ÄĖőĺ_K(s)‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ exp(C¬∑‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ¬∑log ‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ)` for
  `‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ ‚Č• 2`. -/
  growth : ‚ąÉ C : ‚ĄĚ, 0 < C ‚ąß ‚ąÄ s : ‚Ąā, 2 ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ ‚Üí
    ‚ÄĖxi s‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ Real.exp (C * ‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ * Real.log ‚ÄĖs‚ÄĖ)

