  ZLatticePoisson.zlattice_theta_transform L t ht

/-- **Hecke's theta‚ÄďMellin `WeakFEPair` family of the class group**
(sorry node, stated 2026-07-24 ‚ÄĒ the Neukirch VII ¬ß¬ß3‚Äď5 core of the
per-class Hecke continuation, cut out of
`heckeClassZeta_of_zlattice_theta`, whose assembly is PROVEN on top of
this leaf and `weakFEPair_growth`): from the `n`-dimensional lattice
theta law `hőł` (verbatim `zlattice_theta_transform`) produce, for
every ideal class `C`, a `WeakFEPair` `P C` ‚ÄĒ mathlib's abstract
Mellin/functional-equation machine
(`Mathlib.NumberTheory.LSeries.AbstractFuncEq`, instantiated exactly
as `Mathlib.NumberTheory.LSeries.HurwitzZetaEven` does) ‚ÄĒ with

* weight `k = 1/2` and root number `őĶ = 1`;
* one shared constant term `f‚āÄ = g‚āÄ = ŌĀ` (Neukirch VII (5.7)/(5.8):
  the unit-domain theta integral has the SAME limit
