* the Mellin identification on `re s > 1`: the partial Dirichlet
  series of the class converges (`LSeriesSummable`; from the pin's
  per-class ideal-counting asymptotics
  `Ideal.tendsto_norm_le_and_mk_eq_div_atTop` through
  `LSeriesSummable_of_sum_norm_bigO`, or from the theta estimates
  themselves) and
  `őõ(s/2) = |d_K|^{s/2}¬∑őď_‚ĄĚ(s)^{r‚āĀ}¬∑őď_‚Ąā(s)^{r‚āā}¬∑L(a_C, s)` with
  `őď_‚ĄĚ(s) = ŌÄ^{‚ąís/2}¬∑őď(s/2)`, `őď_‚Ąā(s) = 2¬∑(2ŌÄ)^{‚ąís}¬∑őď(s)` (Neukirch
  VII ¬ß4's archimedean Euler factors, via `WeakFEPair.hasMellin` at
  `re (s/2) > 1/2 = k`).

Intended construction (J. Neukirch, *Algebraic Number Theory*, VII
¬ß¬ß3‚Äď5):

1. *Ideal lattices and their duals* (Neukirch VII ¬ß3).  Choose an
   integral ideal `ūĚĒě ‚ąą C‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`; the nonzero integral ideals in `C`
