complex number field of degree `n ‚Č• 48` has root discriminant at
least `33/4 = 8.25 > 314928^{1/6} = 8.2497‚Ä¶`, stated integrally as
`33^n ‚Č§ 4^n¬∑|d_K|`.

This is Odlyzko's unconditional discriminant bound (A. M. Odlyzko,
*Lower bounds for discriminants of number fields*, Acta Arith. 29
(1976); G. Poitou, *Sur les petits discriminants*, S√©m.
Delange‚ÄďPisot‚ÄďPoitou 18 (1976/77), exp. 6, whose table p. 6-17 gives
`13.77` at degree `48`; the asymptote is `4ŌÄe^ő≥ = 22.38‚Ä¶`).
(Minkowski's bound alone, asymptotically `ŌÄe¬≤/4 = 5.803‚Ä¶`, does NOT
suffice for this statement, and the plain Stark-lemma bound tops out
near `7` at degree 48 ‚ÄĒ hence the explicit-formula leaf.)  The
assembly: with `ő≥ > 1/2` (mathlib), `J ‚Č§ 5/8` and `C ‚Č§ 3` (the two
integral leaves), the explicit-formula leaf gives
`log |d_K| ‚Č• n(ő≥ + log 4ŌÄ ‚ąí 5/8) ‚ąí 12 ‚Č• n(log 4ŌÄ ‚ąí 1/8) ‚ąí 12`, and
`log 4ŌÄ ‚ąí 1/8 ‚ąí log (33/4) = log (16ŌÄ/33) ‚ąí 1/8 ‚Č• 3/8 ‚ąí 1/8 = 1/4`
(via `e^{3/8} < 1.46` from `e¬≥ < 1.46‚Āł` and `33¬∑1.46 < 16¬∑3.14 <
16ŌÄ`), so `log |d_K| ‚ąí n¬∑log (33/4) ‚Č• n/4 ‚ąí 12 ‚Č• 0` for `n ‚Č• 48`. -/
theorem odlyzko_rootDiscr_totallyComplex (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K]
    (htc : NumberField.IsTotallyComplex K)
    (hdeg : 48 ‚Č§ Module.finrank ‚Ąö K) :
    (33 : ‚Ą§) ^ Module.finrank ‚Ąö K ‚Č§
      4 ^ Module.finrank ‚Ąö K * |NumberField.discr K| := by
  set n := Module.finrank ‚Ąö K with hn
  have hA := poitou_explicit_formula_bound K htc
  have hB := integral_one_sub_odlyzkoTestFn_div_sinh_le
  have hC := integral_odlyzkoTestFn_le
  have hő≥ : (1 : ‚ĄĚ) / 2 < Real.eulerMascheroniConstant :=
    Real.one_half_lt_eulerMascheroniConstant
  -- `e^{3/8} < 1.46`, via eighth powers: `e¬≥ < 2.7182818286¬≥ < 1.46‚Āł`
  have hexp : Real.exp (3 / 8) < 1.46 := by
    refine lt_of_pow_lt_pow_left‚āÄ 8 (by norm_num) ?_
    have h8 : Real.exp (3 / 8) ^ (8 : ‚Ąē) = Real.exp 3 := by
      rw [‚Üź Real.exp_nat_mul]; norm_num
    have h3 : Real.exp 3 = Real.exp 1 ^ (3 : ‚Ąē) := by
      rw [‚Üź Real.exp_nat_mul]; norm_num
