set_option backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false in
/-- **Ramified inertia at a prime dividing the radicand** (PROVEN
2026-07-23 ‚ÄĒ the ramification half of the quadratic-field
classification): in the setting of `exists_quadratic_generator`
(`Gal(K/‚Ąö) = {1, ŌÉ}`, `x¬≤ = d ‚ąą ‚Ą§` squarefree, `ŌÉ x = ‚ąíx`), for any
prime `q ‚ą£ d` and any prime `Q` of `ūĚďě K` above `q`, the nontrivial
automorphism `ŌÉ` lies in the inertia subgroup of `Q`. Argument, for
`y ‚ąą ūĚďě K` with `t = ŌÉ y ‚ąí y`: both `t¬≤` and `t¬∑x` are Galois-invariant
(ŌÉ negates both `t` and `x`) integral elements, hence rational
integers `s` and `m` with `m¬≤ = d¬∑s`; `q ‚ą£ d` squarefree forces
`q ‚ą£ s` (`q ‚ą£ m¬≤` ‚áí `q ‚ą£ m` ‚áí `q¬≤ ‚ą£ d¬∑s` ‚áí `q ‚ą£ (d/q)¬∑s`, and
`q ‚ą§ d/q`); so `t¬≤ = s ‚ąą q¬∑ūĚďěK ‚äÜ Q` and `t ‚ąą Q` by primality. -/
theorem mem_inertia_of_dvd_squarefree
    (K : IntermediateField ‚Ąö (AlgebraicClosure ‚Ąö)) [NumberField K]
    [IsGalois ‚Ąö K] (ŌÉ : K ‚ČÉ‚āź[‚Ąö] K) (hŌÉ2 : ŌÉ * ŌÉ = 1)
    (huniv : ‚ąÄ g : K ‚ČÉ‚āź[‚Ąö] K, g = 1 ‚ą® g = ŌÉ)
    (x : K) (hxŌÉ : ŌÉ x = -x) {d : ‚Ą§} (hdsq : Squarefree d)
    (hx2 : x ^ 2 = (d : K)) {q : ‚Ąē} (hq : q.Prime) (hqd : (q : ‚Ą§) ‚ą£ d)
    (Q : Ideal (NumberField.RingOfIntegers K)) [Q.IsPrime]
    (hQmem : ((q : ‚Ąē) : NumberField.RingOfIntegers K) ‚ąą Q) :
    ŌÉ ‚ąą Q.inertia (K ‚ČÉ‚āź[‚Ąö] K) := by
  classical
  have hqZ : Prime ((q : ‚Ą§)) := Nat.prime_iff_prime_int.mp hq
  -- `d = q¬∑d'` with `q ‚ą§ d'` (squarefreeness)
