fields `‚Ąö(‚ąöd)`, `d ‚ąą {-1, 2, -2, 3, -3, 6, -6}`: there is a square
root `x` of `d` in `‚ĄöŠĶÉň°ŠĶć` such that `őł g = 1` exactly when `g` fixes
`x`. Content: the fixed field `K` of `ker őł` is a degree-2 Galois
