unique squarefree integer `d ‚ąČ {0, 1}`; an odd prime `q` dividing `d`
ramifies in `‚Ąö(‚ąöd)` (the different of `‚Ą§[‚ąöd]‚āö` at `q ‚ą£ d` is
divisible by `‚ąöd`), so the inertia at `q` acts nontrivially on `K`,
i.e. maps outside `ker őł` ‚ÄĒ contradicting the unramifiedness
hypothesis unless `q ‚ąą {3}`; hence the squarefree `d` divides `6`,
