/-- **No common eigenvector under absolute irreducibility** (PROVEN
2026-07-23 ‚ÄĒ the transport bridge for the induced-structure glue of
the dihedral ray-class decomposition): if every matrix `u g` of the
transported representation has the SAME eigenvector `v ‚Č† 0` over
`Dickson.K 3`, then the vector of `(AlgebraicClosure k) ‚äó V` with
`e`-preimage coordinates `v` in the basis `b` spans a stable line,
contradicting absolute irreducibility (`isIrreducible_iff_forall`
plus `finrank_span_singleton = 1 ‚Č† 2`). -/
theorem no_common_eigenvector_of_absolutelyIrreducible {k : Type u}
    [Finite k] [Field k]
    [Algebra ‚Ą§_[3] k] [TopologicalSpace k] [DiscreteTopology k]
    (V : Type*) [AddCommGroup V] [Module k V] [Module.Finite k V]
    [Module.Free k V]
    (hV : Module.rank k V = 2) {ŌĀ : GaloisRep ‚Ąö k V}
    (habs : Slop.OddRep.IsAbsolutelyIrreducible
      (MonoidHomClass.toMonoidHom ŌĀ : Representation k (őď ‚Ąö) V))
    (b : Module.Basis (Fin 2) (AlgebraicClosure k)
      ((AlgebraicClosure k) ‚äó[k] V))
    (e : AlgebraicClosure k ‚ČÉ+* Dickson.K 3)
    (u : őď ‚Ąö ‚Üí* GL (Fin 2) (Dickson.K 3))
    (hu : ‚ąÄ g, ((u g : GL (Fin 2) (Dickson.K 3)) :
      Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) (Dickson.K 3)) =
      (LinearMap.toMatrix b b ((Slop.OddRep.baseChange (AlgebraicClosure k)
        (MonoidHomClass.toMonoidHom ŌĀ)) g)).map e)
    (v : Fin 2 ‚Üí Dickson.K 3) (hv : v ‚Č† 0)
    (hall : ‚ąÄ g : őď ‚Ąö, ‚ąÉ c : Dickson.K 3,
      Matrix.mulVec ((u g : GL (Fin 2) (Dickson.K 3)) :
        Matrix (Fin 2) (Fin 2) (Dickson.K 3)) v = c ‚ÄĘ v) :
    False := by
